          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Nationwide Injunction Abuse Prevention Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill limits the authority of federal district courts to issue injunctions. </p> <p>Specifically, it prohibits a district court from issuing an injunction unless the injunction applies only to one of the following: </p> <ul> <li>the parties to the case before that district court, or </li> <li>the judicial district in which the injunction is issued. </li> </ul>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <updateDate>2019-09-11T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
